    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for oci-seccomp-bpf-hook.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "OCI Hook to generate seccomp json files based on EBF syscalls used by container oci-seccomp-bpf-hook provides a library for applications looking to use the Container Pod concept popularized by Kubernetes.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* net: golang: Go net package: Denial of Service via long CNAME response in LookupCNAME (CVE-2026-33811)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
